            "topic": "Operators — Intermediate Level",
            "theory": "**Logical Operators** combine boolean expressions:\n- `and` — True if both operands are True: `True and False → False`\n- `or` — True if at least one operand is True: `True or False → True`\n- `not` — negates: `not True → False`\n\n**Augmented Assignment Operators** are shorthand:\n`x += 5` is the same as `x = x + 5`\nSimilarly: `-=`, `*=`, `/=`, `//=`, `%=`, `**=`\n\n**Bitwise Operators** work on integer bits:\n- `&` AND, `|` OR, `^` XOR, `~` NOT, `<<` left shift, `>>` right shift\n`5 & 3 → 1`, `5 | 3 → 7`, `5 ^ 3 → 6`",
